Interface EditableFrontier

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Frontier
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    BestFirstFrontier

    public interface EditableFrontier
extends Frontier
    An Editable Frontier is a Frontier from which you can remove nodes according to their terminal state as well as according to the defined remove operation
    Author:
    Simon Campbell

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Node remove(State state)
      If the frontier is not empty, and contains a node with the provide State as its terminus, the node is removed.

      • Methods inherited from interface search.Frontier

        add, clear, getMaxFrontierSize, isEmpty, remove

    • Method Detail

      • remove

        Node remove(State state)
        If the frontier is not empty, and contains a node with the provide State as its terminus, the node is removed. If there are multiple copies of the state in the frontier only one is removed. Otherwise, returns null.
        Parameters:
        state - - the state to find in the frontier and remove
        Returns:
        the Node removed
